\title{Stock-flow descent as coordination game}
\taxon{definition}
\import{macros}

\p{Stage 3 (descent / gluing) is a \strong{coordination game} whose
compositional structure comes from stock-flow diagrams
([[stock-flow-2023]]).}

\p{Local patches are \strong{stocks} (accumulated state). Gluing maps
are \strong{flows} (state transfer between patches). The descent condition
— local sections glue to a global section — is the Nash equilibrium:
no patch can unilaterally change its local section and still be consistent
with its neighbors.}

\p{Stratified composition ([[libkind-epidemic-2022]]) enables hierarchical
gluing: first compose within brain regions (alpha-band patches), then
across regions (cross-frequency coupling). Each level is a stock-flow
game; the hierarchy is the double operadic composition
([[libkind-double-operads-2025]]).}

\p{Effective descent (the core theorem from the stacks-project substrate)
becomes: the coordination game has a unique Nash equilibrium, and it is
computable in real-time (< 1.0ms budget for Stage 3).}
